<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-05-26T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-05-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="116" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d116">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851.5123/25: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-05-26T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 26,
                                        1925—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received May 26—8:36
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>293. Embassy in receipt of various complaints from American citizens
                            because in certain instances they have to pay higher income taxes than
                            French citizens (see last paragraph my despatch number 4737 of January 7
                            last). Request instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>